{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"CORPUS INVALIDATION + CORRECTED DESIGN (operator-flagged, 2026-07-16). The finding-adjudication corpus LABELS are INVALID and Gerrit change 735 is ABANDONED.\n\nROOT CAUSE (two orthogonal confounds, both in the adjudication tooling, NEITHER in production):\n1. TRUNCATION: adjudicate.py capped plan text at PLAN_CAP=6000 chars; production (orchestrator.assemble_context) reviews the WHOLE plan + children, never truncated. 56% of the 400 findings sit on plans >6000 chars -> the rater saw less than production.\n2. NO GROUNDING: adjudicate.py ran a single messages.create with NO tools; production runs 16 criteria (A1,E4,G1G2,G3,G4,G6,G7,T1,T3,T5c,T8,T10,T11,T13,T14,removal-rationale) as AGENTIC finders that grep the codebase (pai_tools.filesystem_tools+grounding_tools+rebar_tools). 55% of findings are on such criteria; the rater could not do what production does.\nCOMBINED: 316/400 (79%) findings contaminated; only 84 (21%) methodologically clean. kappa subset 82% contaminated.\n\nHUMAN ADJUDICATION IS ALSO INVALIDATED (operator's point): the 30 disputes were SELECTED by the faulty A/B process (both truncated+tool-less), the human was ANCHORED on faulty rater rationales, and 17/30 disputes are on agentic criteria where neither rater nor the human systematically grounded in code. So the label layer (LLM + human), disputes.jsonl, dispute_worksheet.md, the kappa figures, and the README validity section are all invalid.\n\nSURVIVES: outcome_corpus.jsonl (mined from events, never LLM-labeled), the finding SAMPLE (production outputs; the stratified 300+100 draw is reusable), the harness/rubrics/SOTA report as machinery.\n\nCORRECTED APPROACH (reuse production code so the adjudicator is a faithful/stronger analog): (a) whole context via orchestrator.assemble_context (no cap, includes children); (b) code-claim classification is the DETERMINISTIC plan_review_grounding op (keyed on the criterion's registered grounding), not an LLM guess; (c) GROUNDED judging via get_runner(cfg) in execution_mode=agentic bound to the finding's REVIEW-TIME code root, reusing pai_tools -> the adjudicator greps real code; (d) validity/impact via the production decide layer (pass3_over_findings/impact_plan/decide.validity). HUMAN audit stays the authoritative ground truth, shown the GROUNDED evidence (not raw rationales); reliability becomes grounded-verifier-vs-human agreement (which localizes the Pass-2 sub-questions/axes that miscalibrate). No new gate, no truncation, no tool-less pass, no multi-unreliable-rater panel. E1 stays in_progress; the corrected corpus replaces the abandoned one in a fresh change."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784235121241233001,"uuid":"3cdbbf41-434c-4a49-9730-2a5bb1dfe2d6"}